 1→//! Managed Chrome/Chromium with CDP, profile isolation per browser ID.
 2→//! Used by the browser tool for screenshots, snapshots, and page interaction.
 3→//!
 4→//! # Features
 5→//!
 6→//! - **navigate**: Navigate to URLs and wait for page load
 7→//! - **screenshot**: Capture page screenshots (full page or viewport)
 8→//! - **snapshot**: Extract DOM with numbered element references
 9→//! - **click**: Click elements by reference number
10→//! - **type**: Type text into input fields
11→//! - **scroll**: Scroll the page or specific elements
12→//! - **evaluate**: Execute JavaScript in page context
13→//! - **wait**: Wait for elements to appear
14→//!
15→//! # Example
16→//!
17→//! ```ignore
18→//! use moltis_browser::{BrowserManager, BrowserConfig, BrowserRequest, BrowserAction};
19→//!
20→//! let config = BrowserConfig { enabled: true, ..Default::default() };
21→//! let manager = BrowserManager::new(config);
22→//!
23→//! let request = BrowserRequest {
24→//!     session_id: None,
25→//!     action: BrowserAction::Navigate { url: "https://example.com".into() },
26→//!     timeout_ms: 30000,
27→//! };
28→//!
29→//! let response = manager.handle_request(request).await;
30→//! ```
